# Desktop Signed-Out Onboarding UI Implementation Plan

## Overview

Replace the minimal bare-button signed-out state in `apps/desktop` with a Codex-inspired onboarding screen: centered Lightfast monogram, "Welcome to Lightfast" heading, "The superintelligence layer for teams and agents" subtitle, and a two-button column (primary **Sign in with Lightfast**, secondary **Learn more**). Full-window overlay so the unauthed user is not shown sidebar navigation they cannot use.

Visual reference: `/Applications/Codex.app` (OpenAI Codex Electron app) onboarding login page. We port the **layout and interaction pattern**, not branding.

> **Relationship to desktop-clerk-trpc-wiring.md Phase 5**: this plan is the visual follow-up to Phase 5. Phase 5 has already landed the React bootstrap, the bare signed-out branch (`app-shell.tsx:29–40`), and the signed-in `AccountCard` path. This plan replaces only the signed-out JSX and touches neither Phase 5's tRPC wiring, `account-card.tsx`, nor the signed-in branch. Land Phase 5 first; this sits on top of it.

## Current State Analysis

### What exists

- **`apps/desktop/src/renderer/src/react/app-shell.tsx:29–40`** — existing signed-out branch: a single unstyled `<button>` inside `<div class="auth-gate">`. Triggers `window.lightfastBridge.auth.signIn()` (Phase 4's BrowserWindow flow).
- **`apps/desktop/src/renderer/src/styles.css`** — vanilla CSS with existing design tokens:
  - `--color-background-surface`, `--color-background-surface-under`
  - `--color-background-elevated-primary`, `--color-background-elevated-secondary`
  - `--color-text-foreground`, `--color-text-foreground-secondary`, `--color-text-foreground-tertiary`
  - `--color-border`, `--color-border-heavy`
  - `--spacing` (`0.25rem`), `--text-base` (13px), `--text-sm` (12px)
  - `--height-toolbar` (46px) — reserved for titlebar drag region
  - Existing `.action` button (`styles.css:335–350`) is the nearest thing to a secondary/outline button: `background: var(--color-background-elevated-secondary); border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 6px; cursor: default` — we mirror its pattern.
  - **No existing primary/filled button class** — introduced here.
- **`apps/desktop/src/renderer/index.html:74–100`** — React mount point is `#react-root` inside the `home` content pane, which lives alongside the sidebar (`aside.sidebar`) under `#app`. To cover the sidebar we need a `position: fixed; inset: 0` overlay, not just content-pane fill.
- **`apps/desktop/src/shared/ipc.ts:9,122`**, **`apps/desktop/src/main/index.ts:182–189`**, **`apps/desktop/src/preload/preload.ts:74`** — `window.lightfastBridge.openExternal(url)` already plumbed end-to-end. Secondary "Learn more" can call it directly; **no main-process changes needed**.
- **`packages/ui/src/components/icons.tsx:19–34`** — `Icons.logoShort` is a standalone `currentColor` SVG (`viewBox="0 0 194 194"`) depicting the Lightfast monogram. We inline the path data rather than adding `@repo/ui` as a workspace dep.
- **`html.electron-dark` / `html.electron-light`** (`styles.css:28,78`) — theme tokens switch via class on `<html>`. Anything using `var(--color-*)` adapts automatically.
- **`-webkit-app-region: drag` / `no-drag`** — used throughout existing DOM (`index.html:12,50`, `.sidebar .titlebar-drag`). Required on macOS so users can drag the window by the top strip. Must be preserved when the overlay renders.

### Codex reference (decompiled from `/Applications/Codex.app/Contents/Resources/app.asar`)

Pseudo-JSX from the onboarding-login bundle. Locate by `grep -r "electron.onboarding.login.title" webview/assets/` after extracting — asset filenames are Vite-hashed and change on every Codex release:

```
<button aria-label="Play Snake">                       <!-- easter egg, not ported -->
  <Logo size={48} animation="hello" />
</button>
<!-- Fragment: -->
<span class="mt-4 text-heading-lg font-medium">        Welcome to Codex              </span>
<span class="mt-1 text-lg description-foreground">    The best way to build with agents </span>
<div class="mt-8 flex flex-col items-center">
  <div class="w-full max-w-[200px] flex flex-col gap-3">
    <Button primary py-2.5 w-full>  Continue with ChatGPT  </Button>
    <Button outline py-2.5 w-full>  Enter API key          </Button>
  </div>
</div>
```

Spacing hierarchy we port 1:1 (Tailwind → custom-property equivalents): `mt-4` → `16px` (logo → title), `mt-1` → `4px` (title → subtitle), `mt-8` → `32px` (subtitle → actions), button column `max-width: 200px`, button column `gap: 12px`, buttons `padding-block: 10px` (`py-2.5`).

## Desired End State

- Unauthed launch: desktop primary window shows a centered Lightfast monogram, "Welcome to Lightfast" heading, "The superintelligence layer for teams and agents" subtitle, and two stacked buttons — "Sign in with Lightfast" (primary, filled) and "Learn more" (secondary, outline).
- Sidebar + existing home content is fully hidden while unauthed (overlay covers them).
- Titlebar drag region still works in the overlay's top strip; traffic-light buttons visible and functional.
- Dark + light theme both render correctly via existing `.electron-dark` / `.electron-light` tokens.
- Click "Sign in with Lightfast" → triggers Phase 4's BrowserWindow flow. On success, the overlay unmounts and the signed-in UI (account card + sign-out button from Phase 5) renders.
- Click "Learn more" → opens `https://lightfast.ai` in the user's default system browser (via existing `openExternal` IPC).
- Negative paths: closing the sign-in BrowserWindow before completing the Clerk flow leaves the overlay exactly as-is; closing the window or crashing the renderer does not leak the overlay over a signed-in state.

### Verification

- `pnpm --filter @lightfast/desktop typecheck` passes.
- `pnpm --filter @lightfast/desktop dev` boots cleanly.
- Visual side-by-side with `/Applications/Codex.app` (signed-out state) shows matching layout proportions: logo size, vertical rhythm, button column width, button padding.
- Toggling theme (`html.electron-dark` ↔ `html.electron-light`) produces readable contrast in both modes.

### Key Discoveries

- `window.lightfastBridge.openExternal` already works (`apps/desktop/src/preload/preload.ts:74`) — no IPC changes for "Learn more".
- Desktop renderer uses **vanilla CSS + CSS custom properties**, NOT Tailwind (`styles.css:1`). Codex's utility-class layout translates to explicit `var(--spacing)` math.
- `Icons.logoShort` SVG from `packages/ui/src/components/icons.tsx:19–34` is `currentColor`-clean; safe to inline.
- `.action` (`styles.css:335–350`) is the existing tertiary/outline pattern we mirror for the secondary button. Primary filled style is new.
- Overlay must be `position: fixed; inset: 0` — the React root is mounted inside a content pane adjacent to the sidebar, so pane-fill (`100% width/height`) would leave the sidebar visible.

## What We're NOT Doing

- **Not porting Codex's Snake easter egg.** Clickable-logo-starts-game is ~200 LOC of game canvas + audio; out of scope.
- **Not porting the API-key entry flow.** Lightfast has a single sign-in path (Clerk via BrowserWindow); there is no API-key concept to expose.
- **Not adding animations.** No logo shimmer, no fade-in, no "hello" animation. Can revisit after first ship.
- **Not refactoring `Icons.logoShort`** into a shared package for desktop. Inline the path; revisit if a third inliner appears.
- **Not touching `AccountCard` or the signed-in branch of `AppShell`.** This plan is strictly the `!auth.isSignedIn` render path.
- **Not wiring error/toast surfaces for sign-in failures** beyond what Phase 4/5 already do. A silent return-to-overlay on BrowserWindow dismissal is sufficient.
- **Not adding a "Forgot / trouble signing in?" helper link** this iteration.

## Implementation Approach

Two small files, one CSS additive. No existing code is deleted or restructured — only the 10-line signed-out JSX in `app-shell.tsx` is swapped for a single `<SignedOutShell />` element.

---

## Phase 1: Signed-out shell component

### Overview

Create a self-contained React component that renders the full-window overlay with the Codex-inspired layout.

### Changes Required

#### 1.1 New component file

**File**: `apps/desktop/src/renderer/src/react/signed-out-shell.tsx` (new)

```tsx
interface SignedOutShellProps {
  onSignIn: () => void;
  onLearnMore: () => void;
}

export function SignedOutShell({ onSignIn, onLearnMore }: SignedOutShellProps) {
  return (
    <div className="auth-gate" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="auth-gate-title">
      <div className="auth-gate__titlebar-drag" aria-hidden="true" />
      <div className="auth-gate__content">
        <LightfastMonogram className="auth-gate__logo" />
        <h1 id="auth-gate-title" className="auth-gate__title">
          Welcome to Lightfast
        </h1>
        <p className="auth-gate__subtitle">The superintelligence layer for teams and agents</p>
        <div className="auth-gate__actions">
          <button
            type="button"
            className="auth-gate__primary-button"
            onClick={onSignIn}
          >
            Sign in with Lightfast
          </button>
          <button
            type="button"
            className="auth-gate__secondary-button"
            onClick={onLearnMore}
          >
            Learn more
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}

function LightfastMonogram({ className }: { className?: string }) {
  // Source of truth: packages/ui/src/components/icons.tsx:19–34 (Icons.logoShort).
  // Re-copy the path data on logo change. `@repo/ui` is not a dep of apps/desktop.
  return (
    <svg
      className={className}
      viewBox="0 0 194 194"
      fill="none"
      xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
      aria-hidden="true"
    >
      <path
        d="<PATH_DATA_FROM_Icons.logoShort>"
        stroke="currentColor"
        strokeLinecap="round"
        strokeLinejoin="round"
        strokeWidth="14"
      />
    </svg>
  );
}
```

> **Path data**: copy verbatim from `packages/ui/src/components/icons.tsx:26–27`. The inline placeholder above is for plan readability only — the implementation must paste the full path string.

> **Why `<p>` not `<span>` for subtitle**: Codex uses `<span>` for both title and subtitle, but our semantic tree benefits from `<h1>` + `<p>` (the subtitle is prose, not a secondary title). Screen reader experience improves.

#### 1.2 Wire into `AppShell`

**File**: `apps/desktop/src/renderer/src/react/app-shell.tsx`
**Changes**: Replace lines 29–40 with a single `<SignedOutShell />` element. Import added at the top.

```tsx
import { SignedOutShell } from "./signed-out-shell";

// …inside AppShell, replacing lines 29–40:
if (!auth.isSignedIn) {
  return (
    <SignedOutShell
      onSignIn={() => void window.lightfastBridge.auth.signIn()}
      onLearnMore={() =>
        void window.lightfastBridge.openExternal("https://lightfast.ai")
      }
    />
  );
}
```

> **Why two explicit callbacks instead of passing `lightfastBridge` through**: the shell stays a dumb presentation component, easy to snapshot-test later without an Electron mock. The bridge plumbing stays co-located with the existing auth-state logic in `AppShell`.

### Success Criteria

#### Automated Verification

- [ ] `pnpm --filter @lightfast/desktop typecheck` passes
- [ ] `SignedOutShell` renders without console errors when `pnpm --filter @lightfast/desktop dev` is running and the app is signed out (check devtools console)

#### Manual Verification

- [ ] Launch desktop signed-out — overlay renders, sidebar not visible
- [ ] Logo is visible, sized 48×48, uses foreground color in both themes
- [ ] Title "Welcome to Lightfast" rendered below logo, 16px gap
- [ ] Subtitle "The superintelligence layer for teams and agents" rendered below title, 4px gap
- [ ] Two-button column below subtitle with 32px gap
- [ ] Primary button "Sign in with Lightfast" is filled; "Learn more" is outline
- [ ] Primary button click triggers `window.lightfastBridge.auth.signIn()` (Phase 4 BrowserWindow opens)
- [ ] "Learn more" click opens `https://lightfast.ai` in the system browser (not in Electron)

---

## Phase 2: Overlay CSS + theme parity

### Overview

Append overlay + button styles to `styles.css`. All rules use existing custom properties so both `.electron-dark` and `.electron-light` themes render correctly with zero extra color logic.

### Changes Required

#### 2.1 Append to `apps/desktop/src/renderer/src/styles.css`

Add at the end of the file (after existing rules, before any trailing `@media` blocks if present):

```css
/* Signed-out onboarding overlay */

.auth-gate {
  position: fixed;
  inset: 0;
  z-index: 10;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  background: var(--color-background-surface);
  color: var(--color-text-foreground);
  -webkit-app-region: drag;
}

.auth-gate__titlebar-drag {
  flex-shrink: 0;
  height: var(--height-toolbar);
}

.auth-gate__content {
  flex: 1;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  padding: calc(var(--spacing) * 8);
  -webkit-app-region: no-drag;
}

.auth-gate__logo {
  width: 48px;
  height: 48px;
  color: var(--color-text-foreground);
}

.auth-gate__title {
  margin: calc(var(--spacing) * 4) 0 0;
  font-size: 20px;
  font-weight: 500;
  color: var(--color-text-foreground);
  text-align: center;
}

.auth-gate__subtitle {
  margin: calc(var(--spacing) * 1) 0 0;
  font-size: 15px;
  font-weight: 400;
  color: var(--color-text-foreground-secondary);
  text-align: center;
}

.auth-gate__actions {
  margin-top: calc(var(--spacing) * 8);
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: calc(var(--spacing) * 3);
  width: 100%;
  max-width: 200px;
}

.auth-gate__primary-button,
.auth-gate__secondary-button {
  padding: calc(var(--spacing) * 2.5) calc(var(--spacing) * 4);
  font-size: var(--text-base);
  border-radius: 6px;
  cursor: default;
  appearance: none;
  transition: background 120ms ease, border-color 120ms ease, opacity 120ms ease;
}

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .auth-gate__primary-button,
  .auth-gate__secondary-button {
    transition: none;
  }
}

.auth-gate__primary-button {
  font-weight: 500;
  color: var(--color-background-surface);
  background: var(--color-text-foreground);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-text-foreground);
}

.auth-gate__primary-button:hover {
  opacity: 0.88;
}

.auth-gate__secondary-button {
  font-weight: 400;
  color: var(--color-text-foreground);
  background: transparent;
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
}

.auth-gate__secondary-button:hover {
  background: var(--color-background-elevated-secondary);
  border-color: var(--color-border-heavy);
}

.auth-gate__primary-button:focus-visible,
.auth-gate__secondary-button:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--color-accent);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}
```

> **Primary color strategy**: the primary button inverts `--color-text-foreground` (fg becomes bg) — guarantees contrast in both themes without introducing a new brand-color token. If a dedicated brand/primary color is later introduced to the design system, swap both `background` and `border` to it here.

> **Border radius `6px`**: matches every existing desktop button (`.action`, `.error-overlay__reload`, `.item`). This keeps the signed-out CTA consistent with the broader desktop button system. If the design system later adopts pill/marketing-scale CTAs, migrate all buttons together.

> **Why `z-index: 10`**: sidebar is at document flow `z-index: auto`; `10` guarantees overlay is above it. The fatal-error overlay (`#lightfast-desktop-error-overlay`) sits at `z-index: 9999`, so it correctly wins if an error occurs while the auth overlay is visible. Secondary/HUD windows render in separate `BrowserWindow`s and don't need coordination.

#### 2.2 Reduced-motion affordance

Already included inline alongside the button transitions above so the two blocks can't drift apart when the transition list changes.

### Success Criteria

#### Automated Verification

- [ ] `pnpm --filter @lightfast/desktop typecheck` passes (CSS doesn't gate typecheck, but guards against accidental `.tsx` edits)

#### Manual Verification

- [ ] Overlay covers entire window — sidebar and home content pane are not visible beneath it
- [ ] Top 46px of the overlay is a draggable region (click-drag moves the window)
- [ ] Click on buttons does NOT move the window (drag region excludes content)
- [ ] Dark theme: background is `#181818`-ish, text is white, primary button is white with black text
- [ ] Light theme: background is light, text is dark, primary button is dark with light text (toggle by swapping `electron-dark` → `electron-light` on `<html>`)
- [ ] Focus-visible on tabbing through buttons produces a 2px accent outline
- [ ] Hover on primary → opacity dims to 0.88; hover on secondary → background fades in

---

## Phase 3: Visual parity check against Codex.app

### Overview

Side-by-side visual comparison with the installed Codex.app. Not automated — the goal is catching ad-hoc spacing/weight regressions, not pixel-perfect diff.

### Preparation

Codex shows its onboarding login screen only when signed out. If you're already signed into Codex, reset its state:

```bash
# macOS — reset Codex's signed-in state so the onboarding page renders
rm -rf ~/Library/Application\ Support/Codex/Cookies*
rm -rf ~/Library/Application\ Support/Codex/Partitions
# Or: delete ~/Library/Application\ Support/Codex entirely for a full reset (destructive)
```

> **Note**: the `rm -rf` above targets Codex's own userData, not Lightfast's. If you're not comfortable clearing Codex state, skip this step and work from memory / screenshots of Codex's onboarding page instead.

### Changes Required

None — this phase is verification only.

### Success Criteria

#### Manual Verification (side-by-side)

Run both apps simultaneously:

```bash
# Terminal 1
open -a Codex

# Terminal 2 (from repo root)
pnpm dev:desktop
```

Compare visually:

- [ ] **Logo size**: both ~48px tall, similar visual weight
- [ ] **Logo-to-title gap**: both show ~16px vertical rhythm
- [ ] **Title-to-subtitle gap**: both show ~4px (tight coupling)
- [ ] **Subtitle-to-actions gap**: both show ~32px (visual break before CTA)
- [ ] **Button column width**: both cap at ~200px; buttons stretch the full width
- [ ] **Button padding**: both have ~10px vertical inner padding (CTA feels tappable, not dense)
- [ ] **Button-to-button gap**: both show ~12px between primary and secondary
- [ ] **Typography hierarchy**: title is visibly heavier / larger than subtitle; both centered
- [ ] **Centering**: both lay out on the vertical center of the window, not top-anchored

Acceptable divergences:

- Our pill buttons vs Codex's rounded-md buttons (intentional, see 2.1 note)
- Our static logo vs Codex's animated "hello" logo (intentional, deferred)
- Our two-button column vs Codex's (ChatGPT + API key) — different products, same layout shape

Unacceptable divergences — if seen, iterate on CSS:

- Overlay does not cover sidebar
- Titlebar drag region broken (cannot drag window)
- Theme swap produces unreadable contrast
- Buttons misaligned or column exceeds 200px

---

## Phase 4: Interaction smoke tests

### Overview

Verify the signed-out shell interacts correctly with Phase 4 (`auth-flow.ts`) and the existing `openExternal` channel. These tests are manual — the renderer has no test runner configured.

### Changes Required

None.

### Success Criteria

#### Manual Verification — golden path

1. [ ] Desktop launched signed-out → overlay visible
2. [ ] Click **Sign in with Lightfast** → Electron BrowserWindow opens at `http://localhost:3024/desktop/auth?state=…` (NOT the system browser)
3. [ ] Complete Clerk sign-in inside the BrowserWindow → BrowserWindow closes automatically → overlay unmounts → signed-in UI (`<AccountCard />` + Sign out button) renders
4. [ ] Relaunch Electron — token persists from keychain → signed-in UI renders immediately, overlay is never visible
5. [ ] Click **Sign out** in signed-in UI → overlay re-renders immediately

#### Manual Verification — learn-more path

6. [ ] From signed-out overlay, click **Learn more** → `https://lightfast.ai` opens in the default system browser (Safari/Chrome), NOT inside Electron
7. [ ] Desktop window stays on the signed-out overlay (no navigation)

#### Manual Verification — negative paths

8. [ ] Click **Sign in**, then close the BrowserWindow before completing Clerk sign-in → `beginSignIn()` resolves to `null` → overlay stays exactly as-is, primary button re-clickable
9. [ ] Click **Sign in**, let `SIGNIN_TIMEOUT_MS` elapse (5 minutes) → overlay stays as-is, no error, no stuck state (Phase 4 already handles this; we confirm the overlay observes no side-effects)
10. [ ] Toggle `<html>` class between `electron-dark` and `electron-light` via devtools → overlay re-themes instantly, no FOUC

> **Note**: corrupt-token / keychain-failure robustness is owned by the clerk-trpc wiring plan's Phase 1 (auth-store), not this plan.

#### Regression checks

11. [ ] Existing settings route (`#/settings`) still works after sign-in (i.e., overlay doesn't leak above non-home routes once signed in)
12. [ ] Secondary window (Cmd+Shift+N or menu) still opens and is independent of overlay
13. [ ] HUD window still opens and is independent

---

## Testing Strategy

### Unit Tests

None. `SignedOutShell` is a pure presentation component with two callback props — trivial enough that an integration smoke test (Phase 4 above) is sufficient. If `apps/desktop` later gains a test runner (currently has none per `package.json`), consider adding:

- Snapshot test that `SignedOutShell` renders heading/subtitle/button labels
- Click handlers fire the passed callbacks

### Integration Tests

None. The CDP harness added in `apps/desktop/src/main/bootstrap.ts` (per desktop-clerk-trpc-wiring.md Improvement Log) could later drive the overlay through a Playwright session. Not required for first ship.

### Manual Testing Steps

See Phase 3 (visual parity) and Phase 4 (interaction smoke tests).

## Performance Considerations

- Overlay mounts/unmounts are React re-renders of <10 nodes — trivial cost.
- Inlined SVG path data adds ~8 KB to the renderer bundle (`Icons.logoShort`). If a second inlined SVG appears, consider extracting to a shared `desktop-icons.tsx`.
- No network fetches, no animations, no timers — zero runtime cost after mount.

## Migration Notes

- **No data migration.** This replaces inline JSX with a component reference.
- **Rollback**: revert `app-shell.tsx` to the 10-line inline JSX; remove `signed-out-shell.tsx` and the `.auth-gate__*` CSS block. No persistent state touched.

## References

- Existing signed-out branch (to be replaced): `apps/desktop/src/renderer/src/react/app-shell.tsx:29–40`
- Existing CSS tokens: `apps/desktop/src/renderer/src/styles.css:1–76` (`:root`, `.electron-dark`, `.electron-light`)
- Existing outline button pattern (mirrored for secondary): `apps/desktop/src/renderer/src/styles.css:335–350` (`.action`)
- Lightfast monogram source (inlined): `packages/ui/src/components/icons.tsx:19–34` (`Icons.logoShort`)
- `openExternal` IPC (reused for Learn more): `apps/desktop/src/main/index.ts:182–189`, `apps/desktop/src/preload/preload.ts:74`
- Sign-in IPC (reused for primary CTA): `apps/desktop/src/main/index.ts` (Phase 4 `ipcMain.handle(IpcChannels.authSignIn, …)`) + `apps/desktop/src/preload/preload.ts` (Phase 4 `auth.signIn`)
- Codex reference (decompiled): `/Applications/Codex.app/Contents/Resources/app.asar` → locate the onboarding-login bundle by `grep -r "electron.onboarding.login.title" webview/assets/` (asset filenames are Vite-hashed and rotate on every Codex release)
- Sibling plan (Phase 5 context): `thoughts/shared/plans/2026-04-23-desktop-clerk-trpc-wiring.md`

## Improvement Log

### 2026-04-23 — Adversarial review pass

**Copy**
- Subtitle changed from "The OS for startup building" to **"The superintelligence layer for teams and agents"** (user-provided copy; supersedes both the earlier plan text and the `project_lightfast_positioning_os.md` memory line for the desktop signed-out surface).

**Visual consistency**
- Button `border-radius` changed from `999px` (pill) to **`6px`** to match every other button in the desktop renderer (`.action`, `.error-overlay__reload`, `.item`). Avoids creating a one-off CTA shape. If pills are adopted system-wide later, migrate everything together.
- Removed the redundant `font: inherit` + `font-size` pair on buttons — `font: inherit` clobbers the subsequent `font-size`, so only `font-size: var(--text-base)` remains.
- Moved the `prefers-reduced-motion` block adjacent to the transition declaration it disables, so the two can't drift apart.

**Scope trim**
- Dropped Phase 4 step 10 (corrupt `auth.bin` → relaunch). Keychain/token-load robustness is owned by the clerk-trpc wiring plan's Phase 1 (auth-store), not this UI overlay plan. Added a note pointing there.

**Framing**
- Reframed "Independence from desktop-clerk-trpc-wiring.md Phase 5" as "Relationship to …": this plan is the visual follow-up to Phase 5, not an independent track. Phase 5's bare `SignedOutShell` + `AccountCard` have already landed; this plan replaces only the signed-out JSX. Sequencing is explicit: land Phase 5 first.

**Accuracy fixes**
- Codex-reference JS asset filenames (`onboarding-login-content-4SqV_wbF.js`, `index-CxBol07n.js`) are Vite hashes that change on every Codex release. Replaced with a stable grep key (`electron.onboarding.login.title`) in both the Current State Analysis section and the References section.
- Updated the inline-SVG preamble comment: `Icons.logoShort` is the source of truth in `packages/ui/src/components/icons.tsx:19–34`, re-copy on logo change. (`@repo/ui` is not a dep of `apps/desktop` — verified via `apps/desktop/package.json`.)
- Z-index note expanded to document the ladder: `.auth-gate` at `10`, `#lightfast-desktop-error-overlay` at `9999` (styles.css:546–600) — the error overlay correctly wins if a fatal error fires while unauthed.

**Rejected / kept as-is**
- Phase 3 (side-by-side Codex comparison) retained by user preference, including the optional Codex userData reset block (already guarded with a skip-if-uncomfortable note).
- `.auth-gate__content` 32px padding retained — harmless on typical window sizes, provides a safety margin on very small viewports.
- `max-width: 200px` button column retained — "Sign in with Lightfast" measures ~182px (13px font × 22 chars + padding), fits with breathing room.

**Verified but not changed**
- `position: fixed; inset: 0` on the overlay correctly covers the sidebar: no ancestor of `#react-root` uses `transform`, `filter`, `contain`, `perspective`, `will-change`, or `backdrop-filter` (checked `styles.css` end-to-end). The only `transform` in the file is on `.switch__thumb`, which is not an ancestor. No spike needed.
- `.content-inner[data-route-home][data-kind-primary]` is visible in the primary window by default (styles.css:269–279), so the overlay paints on launch. Secondary/HUD windows hide `.sidebar` entirely (styles.css:289–291), so the sidebar-coverage concern is primary-window-only anyway.

